00:21:20,200 --> 00:21:20,700
See you tomorrow.

418
00:21:20,920 --> 00:21:21,460
See you.

419
00:21:21,540 --> 00:21:25,860
[Galaxy Tavern]

420
00:21:28,750 --> 00:21:29,140
You're here.

421
00:21:30,640 --> 00:21:31,140
How much?

422
00:21:32,200 --> 00:21:32,940
Call it drink credit.

423
00:21:34,790 --> 00:21:35,570
You're leaving?

424
00:21:36,750 --> 00:21:37,180
I have something to do.

425
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:40,220
Your uncle and Jialu aren't here either.

426
00:21:40,640 --> 00:21:41,220
Didn't you guys

427
00:21:41,270 --> 00:21:42,180
eat somewhere else?

428
00:21:50,510 --> 00:21:51,290
Be careful.

429
00:21:56,960 --> 00:21:57,700
Would you like this one?

430
00:21:57,960 --> 00:21:58,620
No...

431
00:21:58,720 --> 00:21:59,180
It's too expensive.

432
00:21:59,310 --> 00:21:59,980
- Too expensive? - Come on, order it.

433
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:00,620
Too expensive.

434
00:22:00,640 --> 00:22:01,380
Then forget it.

435
00:22:01,400 --> 00:22:02,150
Do you want this one?

436
00:22:02,150 --> 00:22:02,940
No.

437
00:22:03,240 --> 00:22:04,650
We'll order it next time you treat.

438
00:22:04,650 --> 00:22:05,570
Yeah.

439
00:22:05,600 --> 00:22:06,520
Who, me?

440
00:22:06,520 --> 00:22:07,620
Yeah, next meal's on you.

441
00:22:07,720 --> 00:22:08,400
Abalone.

442
00:22:08,510 --> 00:22:08,990
Abalone...

443
00:22:08,990 --> 00:22:10,180
- I want abalone rice. - Abalone.

444
00:22:10,200 --> 00:22:10,660
Yeah.

445
00:22:10,680 --> 00:22:12,250
- Abalone rice. - He's treating me, not you.

446
00:22:12,480 --> 00:22:13,960
I don't care.

447
00:22:14,110 --> 00:22:14,900
I want the big ones.

448
00:22:15,160 --> 00:22:16,330
One, two, three.

449
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:18,900
More selfies with the abalone rice.

450
00:22:18,960 --> 00:22:20,180
Come on, hold it up.

451
00:22:20,270 --> 00:22:21,180
Bring it up.

452
00:22:21,440 --> 00:22:22,980
Food up by our mouths?

453
00:22:23,030 --> 00:22:23,380
Yeah.

454
00:22:28,200 --> 00:22:28,490
Good.

455
00:22:29,440 --> 00:22:30,660
Hey, don't dig in yet.

456
00:22:30,790 --> 00:22:32,090
Let me snap pics of the dishes first,

457
00:22:32,200 --> 00:22:32,940
and post them on Moments.

458
00:22:33,110 --> 00:22:33,900
When you post them,

459
00:22:33,960 --> 00:22:34,980
remember to block Chu Dan.

460
00:22:35,400 --> 00:22:36,090
And my wife too.

461
00:22:36,200 --> 00:22:36,700
Block her as well.

462
00:22:37,720 --> 00:22:38,380
So she doesn't nag me

463
00:22:38,440 --> 00:22:39,380
for wasting money eating out

464
00:22:39,440 --> 00:22:39,940
instead of doing real work.

465
00:22:41,110 --> 00:22:42,730
Man, why do you live so tied up?

466
00:22:42,850 --> 00:22:43,980
I'm just marking the moment.

467
00:22:44,240 --> 00:22:45,080
Back then,

468
00:22:45,110 --> 00:22:46,180
every time we passed by here,

469
00:22:47,000 --> 00:22:48,180
all I could think was,

470
00:22:48,640 --> 00:22:49,940
"when will my brother ever come in

471
00:22:50,270 --> 00:22:51,660
and treat me to abalone rice?"

472
00:22:51,960 --> 00:22:53,010
But today,

473
00:22:53,270 --> 00:22:54,620
I'm the one treating my brother

474
00:22:54,680 --> 00:22:55,620
to abalone rice right here.

475
00:22:56,640 --> 00:22:57,860
Today really

476
00:22:57,960 --> 00:22:58,940
is worth celebrating.

477
00:22:59,720 --> 00:23:00,180
Jiaqi,

478
00:23:00,400 --> 00:23:00,900
here's to you.

479
00:23:03,960 --> 00:23:04,660
No more words.

480
00:23:05,720 --> 00:23:06,180
Cheers!

481
00:23:06,240 --> 00:23:06,940
- Cheers! - Cheers!

482
00:23:13,200 --> 00:23:13,860
Can we eat now?

483
00:23:14,640 --> 00:23:15,140
Go ahead, dig in.

484
00:23:15,200 --> 00:23:15,620
Come on.

485
00:23:41,720 --> 00:23:42,460
I honestly didn't expect

486
00:23:42,510 --> 00:23:43,900
you two to stick with it this long,

487
00:23:44,920 --> 00:23:45,770
and do so well.

488
00:23:46,110 --> 00:23:47,140
At first, I didn't expect it either.

489
00:23:48,350 --> 00:23:49,180
I thought the job

490
00:23:49,270 --> 00:23:50,660
would be boring and exhausting.

491
00:23:51,960 --> 00:23:52,940
But these days,

492
00:23:53,270 --> 00:23:54,940
I work hard every day,

493
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:57,180
get home and crash.

494
00:23:57,510 --> 00:23:57,980
Stuff like

495
00:23:58,590 --> 00:23:59,700
the sleep issues,

496
00:24:00,200 --> 00:24:00,700
the anxiety...

497
00:24:00,880 --> 00:24:01,900
all gone.

498
00:24:02,350 --> 00:24:03,700
Now I just feel amazing.

499
00:24:05,000 --> 00:24:05,730
Before,

500
00:24:07,350 --> 00:24:08,730
I'd open my eyes and it's already afternoon.

501
00:24:09,720 --> 00:24:10,940
I wasn't even tired,

502
00:24:11,510 --> 00:24:13,010
but I just felt empty.

503
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:14,940
But now,

504
00:24:15,790 --> 00:24:16,730
as soon as it starts getting light,

505
00:24:17,200 --> 00:24:17,980
I'm out the door.

506
00:24:19,160 --> 00:24:19,940
And the moment I step out,

507
00:24:20,750 --> 00:24:21,860
the first morning sunlight

508
00:24:21,880 --> 00:24:22,860
hits my face.

509
00:24:23,310 --> 00:24:24,140
It's beautiful.

510
00:24:24,680 --> 00:24:25,900
In weather this cold,

511
00:24:26,550 --> 00:24:28,290
I'm actually sweating.

512
00:24:28,830 --> 00:24:29,420
And

513
00:24:29,640 --> 00:24:31,050
I'm so warm I'm steaming.

514
00:24:31,110 --> 00:24:31,620
It feels like...

515
00:24:34,960 --> 00:24:37,090
I'm really alive.

516
00:24:44,660 --> 00:24:46,100
